'''''Mózgprocesor''''' (''Brain Processor'') is a Polish [[video game]] published in 1989 by Computer Adventure Studio for [[ZX Spectrum]] and in 1990 for the [[Atari 8-bit computers]]. It was Computer Adventure Studio's first and last game.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://techsty.art.pl/magazyn/ludologiczny/mozgprocesor_en.html|title=Mózgprocesor > Early Polish text adventure games < Techsty 2012 nr 1 (8) (game issue)|last=Pisarski|first=Mariusz|website=techsty.art.pl|access-date=2018-03-19}}</ref> It was created by Piotr Kucharski, Krzysztof Piwowarski and Wiesław Florek, a team of high school students from [[Bochnia]].<ref name="ts-2"/> The team had previously created [[Smok Wawelski (video game)|Smok Wawelski]] in 1987,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://polygamia.pl/opowie-ci-z-krypty-mozgprocesor/|title=Opowieści z krypty: Mózgprocesor {{!}} Polygamia|website=polygamia.pl|date=5 April 2010 |language=pl-PL|access-date=2018-03-19}}</ref> developed in six weeks out of a script created within an hour.<ref name="ts-2"/>

Reviews of "Mózgprocesor" were featured in  Bajtek 10/1989<ref name="bajtek-46">{{cite magazine |last=Przasnyski |first=Marcin |date=October 1989 |title=Mózgprocesor - polska gra tekstowa |trans-title=Mózgprocesor - Polish text adventure |language=pl |url=https://archive.org/details/bajtek198910/page/n9 |access-date=2024-05-23 |magazine=[[Bajtek]] |number=46 |department=Klan Spectrum |publisher=Młodzieżowa Agencja Wydawnicza |page=10 |issn=0860-1674}}</ref> and Top Secret 3/1991,<ref name="ts-5">{{cite magazine |last=Kinowski |first=Rafał |date=May 1991 |title=Mózgprocesor |language=pl |url=https://archive.org/details/TopSecret05/page/n9 |access-date=2024-05-23 |magazine=[[Top Secret (magazine)|Top Secret]] |number=5 |publisher=Spółdzielnia "Bajtek" |page=10 |issn=0867-8480}}</ref> Top Secret 2/1990 also included an interview with developer Piotr Kucharski,<ref name="ts-2">{{cite magazine |last=Wójcik |first=Maja Agata |date=December 1990 |title=Myśli zaprogramowane |trans-title=Programmed thoughts |language=pl |url=https://archive.org/details/TopSecret02/page/n3 |access-date=2024-05-23 |magazine=[[Top Secret (magazine)|Top Secret]] |number=2 |publisher=Spółdzielnia "Bajtek" |page=4 |issn=0867-8480}}</ref> which at the time was unprecedented for a Polish game.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://idn.org.pl/users/lesz/legend/mozgprocesor.html|title=mózgprocesor|website=idn.org.pl|access-date=2018-03-19}}</ref>

Despite the title's massive popularity in Poland, the game was readily pirated which significantly eroded the profits of the young development company and prevented it from releasing a second title.<ref name=":0" /> According to Techsty, it is the most discussed and most developed of all the Polish text-based adventure games.<ref name=":0" /> Gadzetomania thought the title was probably the first, Polish game published in a professional way.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gadzetomania.pl/57828,najpiekniejsze-gry|title=Piękno nieistniejących światów: najwspanialsze widoki w grach wideo|work=Gadżetomania.pl|access-date=2018-03-19|language=pl}}</ref> Logo24 deemed it the first Polish game that did not differ significantly from global standards.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.logo24.pl/Logo24/56,125390,12908554,Top_10__najwazniejsze_polskie_gry.html|title=Top 10: najważniejsze polskie gry|work=Logo24|access-date=2018-03-19|language=pl-PL}}</ref>

